    "actions_taken": [
      "Pre-job safety meeting conducted",
      "Lifting plan followed with four slings attached to riser spider/gimbal",
      "Incident reported to BSEE at 20:53 hours on 29 September 2020"
    ],
    "summary": "On 29 September 2020 at approximately 17:15 hours, a crane lifting a 15-ton riser spider/gimbal on the Noble Globetrotter II made contact with a handrail during the lift. This contact broke a weld holding a guard for hydraulic hoses. The guard (4 feet long, 12 lbs) fell 6 feet 10 inches to a walkway, bounced through a handrail, and fell an additional 9 feet 6 inches to the main deck. No personnel were injured as the area was clear by design of the lift plan.",
    "recommendations": [
      "Install guides inside the hole in the spider to guide it straight up to clear all hazards and achieve better control of the riser spider"
    ],
